The two cables coming out of the load module are simply connected to the load ports. The lamp itself is encased on the top face of the box. In parallel to the lamp there is a smaller lamp, that is positioned inside the box, and can be seen only by either lifting the box or by opening a small peephole located on on of the box faces. Both lamps are not polarized by themselves, however there is a diod located on the 12V line, before both lamps, such that it will allow current to flow only if the 12V and 0V lines are actually energized with 12V and 0V respectively (it will block current if the polarity is switched).

